Sheâ€™s a Park Explorer at Little Talbot Island State Park- DBJ
Grades: K, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5

The white sandy beaches of Little Talbot Island State Park are a nursery for baby shorebirds and sea turtles each spring and summer. Rangers work hard to protect these little ones and their parents to ensure happy and healthy families for generations to come. Learn about beach habitat and the different types of birds and turtles, how they nest and care for their young and what we do to protect them. Hands-on activities will include making a shorebird identification field book, a bird beaks and egg camouflage game, plus a sea turtle survey exercise and shorebird ID with a spotting scope on the beach. Fun patch provided. Park entrance fee included.

*This event is for 2016 registered Girl Scouts, and registered & approved adult volunteers.
* For safety and supervision reasons, troops and individuals are not permitted to bring non-Girl Scouts or siblings. 
*Girl/adult ratios must be followed and adults are expected to stay on the premises during the event. 

$8/girl, $8/adult 
Contact: Brittany McCallister 904.389.3071
